        {"type":0,"content":"Date: 3/18/2026 \\n\\nYesterday: Was able to fix errors and get the android emulator to run correctly and display the basic \\u201chello world\\u201d program created in visual studio. \\n\\nToday/Tomorrow: Since Expo looks like it's something built on top of React Native and it looked a teammate was having a hard time trying to get Expo to run correctly for the project, I just looked through out some different basic app projects I found online to try and familiarize myself with the development process of React Native and to better prepare for creation of the app. For tomorrow, I\\u2019m hoping the Expo bugs will be resolved so we can begin the process of app development but if it\\u2019s not ready yet, I will try to do some of my own coding through the reactnative.dev website since that looks like it has a editable code sections with a built in phone emulator that reacts to changes made in the code. \\n\\nBlockers: Issues with set up of expo project","mentions":[],"mention_roles":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:59:22.582000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"flags":0,"components":[],"id":"1484083849150332938","channel_id":"1478078339632730223","author":{"id":"1390831788905074759","username":"chay_lars","avatar":"cd435ba634eb65a90f37a93ebb396468","discriminator":"0","public_flags":0,"flags":0,"banner":null,"accent_color":null,"global_name":null,"avatar_decoration_data":null,"collectibles":null,"display_name_styles":null,"banner_color":null,"clan":null,"primary_guild":null},"pinned":false,"mention_everyone":false,"tts":false}
